description: A seamless blend of heritage and high design, this brick-and-beam loft in Boston’s iconic Fort Point Channel epitomizes urban luxury. Set in a historic warehouse conversion, it offers 1,080 sq ft of open living space with 13 ft ceilings, original brick and beams, and expansive windows that flood the home with natural light. Anchored by new hardwood floors and striking architectural lines, the space includes a spacious kitchen with granite countertops, custom cabinetry, and premium stainless steel appliances. The layout balances openness and warmth—ideal for quiet mornings or stylish entertaining. An rare expansive private patio provides panoramic views of Fort Point Channel, Martin’s Park, and the Boston skyline—an uncommon outdoor escape in the Seaport. The serene bedroom, reimagined bath, and in-unit laundry add comfort and convenience. Steps from Seaport dining, South Station, and the Financial District, this home is a refined take on modern loft living.
